PELITE FOR SINGLE-BINARY TEST: Instead of shelling out to dumpbin (requires Windows SDK), use the `pelite` crate (0.10) in the test to parse the PE import table. In tests/native_gui/test_single_binary.rs:
    use pelite::pe64::PeFile;
    let data = std::fs::read("target/release-native/handshake-native.exe").unwrap();
    let pe = PeFile::from_bytes(&data).unwrap();
    let imports = pe.imports().unwrap();
    for desc in imports { let dll = desc.dll_name().unwrap(); assert!(is_system_dll(dll), "Non-system DLL: {}", dll); }
  The test binary path must be relative to the workspace root. If the release-native build has not been run before the test, the test should skip with eprintln!('SKIP: release-native binary not found; run cargo build --profile release-native first') and return Ok(()).
